mapping_comments: Task was administered but data was lost from Getting Lost server. Simran coordinated with contact Ford who provided two possible explanations:    1.	Our server went down after the program was started, and stayed down while the participant performed the test. Typically, if the server is down the main menu will halt the user from proceeding, but if it's up when it checks on the main menu but then dies right before the task starts some data can be lost. If this is the case then I apologize for the data loss.  2.	The internet connection was lost at the location of testing. This again requires some unlucky timing to get past the main menu connectivity checks and then have connectivity drop while the task is saving data. Generally, if the connection at the location of testing is unreliable then I would recommend making use of the downloaded version of the tests. This version retains data locally and can re-attempt to sync with the server if it detects that some local data were not uploaded.
